  "datePublished": "2025-12-31",
  "description": "Scrying is a divinatory practice in which a practitioner gazes into a reflective, translucent, or otherwise visually ambiguous surface — a scrying medium — to receive images, impressions, or insights. Common media include crystal balls, dark mirrors, bowls of water, fire, and smoke.\nThe mechanism, from a naturalistic perspective, is pareidolia and hypnagogic imagery: the visual ambiguity of the medium provides a substrate onto which the practitioner\u0026rsquo;s subconscious projects patterns. From a spiritual perspective, the medium serves as a threshold between ordinary perception and a mode of seeing that is not constrained by physical stimulus.\n",
  "name": "scrying",
